 narrative of European and North American art. He was a man with a mission, utterly confident and determined. \n\nSir David Adjaye, the architect perhaps best known for his largest project to date – the Smithsonian Institute’s National Museum of African American History and Culture - champions the ground-breaking life of Okwui Enwezor, who became both his friend and collaborator. He is joined by Chika Okeke-Agulu, one of the foremost scholars of African Art and Professor of African and African Diaspora Art at Princeton University.\n\nPresented by Matthew Parris\nProduced in Bristol by Nicola Humphries"},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p08r61tn.jpg","duration":{"value":1680,"label":"28 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2020-09-15T16:00:50Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qxsb","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qxsb","title":"Great Lives","synopses":{"short":"Biographical series in which guests choose someone who has inspired their lives.","medium":"Biographical series in which guests choose someone who has inspired their lives.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qxsb&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null},{"id":"m000ms0x","type":"playable_item","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:episode:m000ms0y","network":{"id":"bbc_radio_four","key":"radio4","short_title":"Radio 4","logo_url":"https://sounds.files.bbci.co.uk/3.5.0/networks/bbc_radio_four/{type}_{size}.{format}","network_type":"master_brand"},"release":{"date":"2020-09-22T00:00:00Z","label":"22 Sep 2020"},"titles":{"primary":"Great Lives","secondary":"James Graham on John Maynard Keynes","tertiary":null,"entity_title":"James Graham on John Maynard Keynes"},"synopses":{"short":"The acclaimed playwright tells Matthew Parris wh