nd works and a renewed interest in his essays has emerged.\n\nBen Miller plays Lord Featherington in Bridgerton, and he wrote and starred in The Armstrong and Miller Show on Channel Four. \nWith expert contributions from Dr Uttara Nataragen, a founding organiser of The Hazlitt Society and editor of The Hazlitt Review. \n\nPresented by Matthew Parris\nProduced by Nicola Humphries for BBC Bristol"},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p0c1bd86.jpg","duration":{"value":1680,"label":"28 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2021-05-18T16:01:29Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qxsb","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qxsb","title":"Great Lives","synopses":{"short":"Biographical series in which guests choose someone who has inspired their lives.","medium":"Biographical series in which guests choose someone who has inspired their lives.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qxsb&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null},{"id":"m000w9v7","type":"playable_item","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:episode:m000w9v8","network":{"id":"bbc_radio_four","key":"radio4","short_title":"Radio 4","logo_url":"https://sounds.files.bbci.co.uk/3.5.0/networks/bbc_radio_four/{type}_{size}.{format}","network_type":"master_brand"},"release":{"date":"2021-05-25T00:00:00Z","label":"25 May 2021"},"titles":{"primary":"Great Lives","secondary":"Rosie Millard on Edward III","tertiary":null,"entity_title":"Rosie Millard on Edward III"},"synopses":{"short":"Rosie tells Matthew Parris that Edward III was a cultural hero who deserves greater fame.","medium":"Rosie tells Matthew Parris that Edward III was a great leader, a champion of English cultural life, and deserves to be much better known. The expert is Lord Sumption.","long"