han Cruyff painted the chapel, and Barcelona coaches since merely restore or improve it.\"\n\nThe Dutch journalist and author of 'Johan Cruyff: Always on the Attack' Auke Kok, sheds light on Johan's childhood, his early years as an Ajax player, and how Cruyff's stubborn attitude was both a strength and a weakness throughout his life.\n\nProduced for BBC Audio in Bristol by Toby Field\n\nOther guests in the new series include the UK government vaccine taskforce head, Kate Bingham; chef Romy Gill; and BAFTA winner Holly Walsh who has picked the cult sixties writer, BS Johnson."},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p0cn1q7h.jpg","duration":{"value":1680,"label":"28 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2022-08-02T16:00:04Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qxsb","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qxsb","title":"Great Lives","synopses":{"short":"Biographical series in which guests choose someone who has inspired their lives.","medium":"Biographical series in which guests choose someone who has inspired their lives.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qxsb&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null},{"id":"m0019z0k","type":"playable_item","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:episode:m0019z0l","network":{"id":"bbc_radio_four","key":"radio4","short_title":"Radio 4","logo_url":"https://sounds.files.bbci.co.uk/3.5.0/networks/bbc_radio_four/{type}_{size}.{format}","network_type":"master_brand"},"release":{"date":"2022-08-09T00:00:00Z","label":"09 Aug 2022"},"titles":{"primary":"Great Lives","secondary":"Holly Walsh on BS Johnson","tertiary":null,"entity_title":"Holly Walsh on BS Johnson"},"synopses":{"short":"Holly Walsh picks BS Johnson, fiery sixties novelist","medium":"His work includes a book in a box and a book with a hole ... so you can see what's coming up. But BAFTA winning writer Holly Walsh says it is his anger that appeals most to her.","long":"BS Johnson was born in Hammersmith in 1933. A wartime evacuee, he never quite shook a sense of dislocation for the rest of his life. Holly's favourite book, she calls it the gateway drug to his work, is Christie Malry's Own Double-Entry. It's the tale of a disaffected accountant who applies the principles of double-entry book keeping to his own life; any perceived slight permits him to repay the same on somebody else. These stretch from minor acts of personal revenge to poisoning London's water and blowing up the House of Commons.\n\n\"The things I find attractive about him are the things I'm a little bit scared of. His work is so raw - it's so different to how I feel.\" Holly Walsh\n\nJoining Holly and Matthew Parris is the novelist Jonathan Coe, author of The Rotter's Club and Like a Fiery Elephant, an award-winning biography of BS Johnson's life.\n\nThe producer in Bristol is Miles Warde"},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p0crrjvm.jpg","duration":{"value":1680,"label":"28 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2022-08-09T16:00:08Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qxsb","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qxsb","title":"Great Lives","synopses":{"short":"Biographical series in which guests choose someone who has inspired their lives.","medium":"Biographical series in which guests choose someone who has inspired their lives.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qxsb&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null},{"id":"m001b41h","type":"playable_item","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:episode:m001b41j","network":{"id":"bbc_radio_four","key