st Town and Concrete Jungle. Anyway, before The Specials came on, I made a decision: I would pretend to faint in the hope that I could watch the show from the side of the stage. It worked like a dream. I was carried by the bouncers to the wings, and left there. This was probably the most exciting moment of my life, and as I stood there, Terry Hall noticed me and came over to ask if I was okay. Terry Hall, the coolest man in Britain, being kind and showing concern.\"\n\nYears later Terry Hall publicly announced that he'd been abducted by paedophiles as a boy. Jon Ronson immediately remembered the care and concern Terry had shown him and wondered if this was why. \n\nProgramme includes Terry's bandmate, Lynval Golding, giving his first interview since Terry died in December; plus two of his friends, Shaun O'Donnell and Gary Aspden, and the voice of Terry himself.\n\nJon Ronson is the author of Adventures with Extremists and presenter of Things Fell Apart, about the culture wars.\n\nThe producer in Bristol is Miles Warde"},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p0c1bd86.jpg","duration":{"value":1680,"label":"28 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2023-05-16T16:00:00Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qxsb","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qxsb","title":"Great Lives","synopses":{"short":"Biographical series in which guests choose someone who has inspired their lives.","medium":"Biographical series in which guests choose someone who has inspired their lives.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qxsb&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null},{"id":"m001m4rz","type":"playable_item","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:episode:m001m4s1","network":{"id":"bbc_radio_four","key":"radio4","short_title":"