man people to rise up and over throw Hitler.  He was married and had six children, two of whom took their own lives.\n\nLexicographer and word expert on 'Countdown' Susie Dent says German was her first love and she first-read Mann whilst studying at University.  She loves the tension in his work between the pull of one's senses and the desire to stay aloof and detached.  Susie and Matthew are joined by Karolina Watroba, Research fellow in German and Comparative Literature at the University of Oxford.  Karolina was born in Poland where Mann is a huge cultural icon and she first read 'The Magic Mountain' in the summer before she went to University. \n\nFuture subjects in the series include Hattie Jacques and Stamford Raffles, founder of London Zoo and Singapore.\n\nProduced for BBC Audio in Bristol by Toby Field"},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p0c1bd86.jpg","duration":{"value":1680,"label":"28 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2023-08-01T16:00:00Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qxsb","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qxsb","title":"Great Lives","synopses":{"short":"Biographical series in which guests choose someone who has inspired their lives.","medium":"Biographical series in which guests choose someone who has inspired their lives.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qxsb&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null},{"id":"m001pf6n","type":"playable_item","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:episode:m001pf6t","network":{"id":"bbc_radio_four","key":"radio4","short_title":"Radio 4","logo_url":"https://sounds.files.bbci.co.uk/3.5.0/networks/bbc_radio_four/{type}_{size}.{format}","network_type":"master_brand"},"release":{"date":"2023-08-08T00:00:00Z","label":"08 Aug 2023"},"titles":{