ct, whatever she liked.  \n\nDouble-bassist and founder of the Chineke! Orchestra Chi-chi Nwanoku was driving back from a concert when she first heard Jessye Norman singing on the radio.  She remembers being so struck by her voice that she had to pull over and wait until the performance had finished before continuing her journey.  Chi-chi and presenter Matthew Parris explore some of Jessye Norman's work and recordings, and her views on what it means to be a Black woman in classical music.  \n\nChi-chi and Matthew are joined by Kira Thurman, Associate Professor of Musicology at the University of Michigan to help map out the key moments and decisions in Jessye Norman's extraordinary life.\n\nProduced for BBC Audio Bristol by Toby Field"},"image_url":"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/{recipe}/p0c1bd86.jpg","duration":{"value":1680,"label":"28 mins"},"progress":null,"availability":{"from":"2023-09-19T16:00:00Z","to":null,"label":"Available for over a year"},"container":{"type":"brand","id":"b006qxsb","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:brand:b006qxsb","title":"Great Lives","synopses":{"short":"Biographical series in which guests choose someone who has inspired their lives.","medium":"Biographical series in which guests choose someone who has inspired their lives.","long":null},"activities":[]},"uris":[{"type":"latest","id":null,"label":"Latest","uri":"/v2/programmes/playable?container=b006qxsb&sort=sequential&type=episode&experience=domestic"}],"activities":[],"play_context":null,"guidance":{"competition_warning":false,"warnings":null},"recommendation":null},{"id":"m001qtby","type":"playable_item","urn":"urn:bbc:radio:episode:m001qtc5","network":{"id":"bbc_radio_four","key":"radio4","short_title":"Radio 4","logo_url":"https://sounds.files.bbci.co.uk/3.5.0/networks/bbc_radio_four/{type}_{size}.{format}","network_type":"master_brand"},"release":{"date":"2023-09-26T00:00:00Z","label":"26 Sep 2023"},"titles":{"primary":"Great Lives","secondary":"Ken Loach on Gerrard Winstanley","tertiar